<plot>Multicorp, Inc. runs its charismatic spokesman for the U.S. Senate, with the ulterior motive of "buying out" the government. The multinational corporation gives synergy a whole new meaning when it presents an image of the boy next door while staging press conferences, product placements, and even a sex scandal. A More Perfect Union satires corporate control of media and politics to make a serious argument for campaign finance reform, and it eerily and timely reflects political campaigning around the globe.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?013542</url></doc>
